The quality of data in a UV inactivation study should be checked by a simple plot of survival vs. UV fluence. For most organisms, the UV inactivation is well modeled by a first-order equation [66]. That is, the number of infective virus particles, N, is an exponential function of the applied fluence, F
o multiplied by the original amount of infective virus, N
